			<origination label="Creator:" encodinganalog="100"><persname>Crego, Jean Elizabeth</persname></origination>
			<unittitle label="Title:" encodinganalog="245">Jean Elizabeth Crego Papers</unittitle>
			<unitdate type="inclusive" label="Dates:" encodinganalog="245$f">1923-1999</unitdate>
			<physdesc label="Quantity:" encodinganalog="300$a">4 cubic feet (4 boxes)</physdesc>
			<repository label="Repository:" encodinganalog="852$a"><corpname>Archives and Special Collections Library, Vassar College Libraries</corpname></repository>
			<abstract label="Abstract:" encodinganalog="520$a">Correspondence, photographs,
				clippings, and floor plans related Crego's positions at the Vassar College Alumnae
				House and as the Vassar College Class of 1932 Correspondent, as well as some
				personal papers.</abstract>
		</did>
		<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
			<head>Biographical Note</head>
			<p>Jean Elizabeth Crego was born on 7 October 1910 to Martin Henry and Meta Meyer Crego.
				After her graduation from Vassar College in 1932, she went on to work for the
				College, holding many positions, including Decorating Chairman of the Committee on
				Alumnae House, the Class of 1932's Correspondent, and as Class President. In 1956,
				she founded the Crego Lectures in honor of her father Martin H. Crego, as part of
				the Crego Endowment. On 12 December 2005, at the age of 95 years, Jean Crego passed
				away.</p>
		</bioghist>
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
			<head>Scope and Content Note</head>
			<p>Correspondence, photographs, clippings, and floor plans related to Crego's positions at the
				Vassar College Alumnae House and as the Vassar College Class of 1932 Correspondent,
				as well as some personal papers.</p>
		</scopecontent>
